               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410301-name-1064" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-1064" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-1064" type="surname" value="BALDERY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-1064" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT BALDERY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a dealer in stays, and live in London-street, Greenwich. I assigned my property over to John Sharland and another, as trustees—on the 8th of February the prisoner came for work as a straw<lb></lb>bonnet maker—I was in the parlour when she came in—I saw her take a pair of stays, and conceal them on her person—I let her remain till my wife came up—I then called my wife and my servant into the shop, and charged the prisoner with having the stays—she denied it—I sent the ser<lb></lb>vant for a policeman—the prisoner then said, "Don't be hard with me; I will pay you for them"—she produced them from under her cloak.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PRENDERGAST</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> These goods are not your's?.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184103010183"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> They were assigned to my creditors on the 4th of February—John Sharland and another are the trustees—they receive the money for the produce of the stock—the prisoner had worked for my wife occasionally between three and four years—I never knew any thing against her—I be<lb></lb>lieve she said, after the policeman was in the room, that she was going to bargain for them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410301-name-1065" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-1065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-1065" type="surname" value="O'BRIEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-1065" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM O'BRIEN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 192.) I took the prisoner—she was crying, and wished Mr. Baldery not to give her in charge.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
